tplinkVrrpMIB.name: tplinkVrrpMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

tplinkVrrpMIB.description: This MIB describes objects used for managing Virtual Router Redundancy Protocol (VRRP) routers.

tpVrrpGlobalCtrlTable.name: tpVrrpGlobalCtrlTable
tpVrrpGlobalCtrlTable.description: Operations table for a VRRP router which consists of a sequence (i.e., one or more conceptual rows) of 'TpVrrpGlobalCtrlEntry' items.

tpVrrpGlobalCtrlEntry.name: tpVrrpGlobalCtrlEntry
tpVrrpGlobalCtrlEntry.description: An entry in the tpVrrpGlobalCtrlTable containing the operational characteristics of a virtual router. On a VRRP router,a given virtual router is identified by a combination of the VID and VRID.Rows in the table can be modified according to the tpVrrpStatus.

tpVrrpVrid.name: tpVrrpVrid
tpVrrpVrid.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).

tpVrrpMacAddress.name: tpVrrpMacAddress
tpVrrpMacAddress.description: The virtual MAC address of the virtual router.

tpVrrpPrimaryVirtualIp.name: tpVrrpPrimaryVirtualIp
tpVrrpPrimaryVirtualIp.description: This is the IP address listed as the source in VRRP advertisement last received by this virtual router.

tpVrrpRunPriority.name: tpVrrpRunPriority
tpVrrpRunPriority.description: This object specifies the priority to be used for the virtual router master election process. Higher values imply higher priority.A priority of 255 is used for the router that owns the associated IP address(es).

tpVrrpConfigPriority.name: tpVrrpConfigPriority
tpVrrpConfigPriority.description: This object operate the priority to be used for the virtual router master election process.

tpVrrpAdvertisement.name: tpVrrpAdvertisement
tpVrrpAdvertisement.description: The time interval, in seconds, between sending advertisement messages. Only the master router sends VRRP advertisements.

tpVrrpPreeptMode.name: tpVrrpPreeptMode
tpVrrpPreeptMode.description: Controls whether a higher priority virtual router will preempt a lower priority master

tpVrrpTimeDelay.name: tpVrrpTimeDelay
tpVrrpTimeDelay.description: This is object is used to config the delay timer associated with the VRRP.

tpVrrpAuthType.name: tpVrrpAuthType
tpVrrpAuthType.description: Authentication type used for VRRP protocol exchanges between virtual routers. This value of this object is the same for a given ifindex(Vlan ID).

tpVrrpKey.name: tpVrrpKey
tpVrrpKey.description: The Authentication Key. This object is set according to the value of the 'tpVrrpAuthType' object ('Simple' or 'MD5').

tpVrrpState.name: tpVrrpState
tpVrrpState.description: The current state of the virtual router. This object has three defined values: - `initialize', which indicates that all the virtual router is waiting for a startup event. - `backup', which indicates the virtual router is monitoring the availability of the master router. - `master', which indicates that the virtual router is forwarding packets for IP addresses that are associated with this router.

tpVrrpStatus.name: tpVrrpStatus
tpVrrpStatus.description: The following values are states: these values may be used as follow: active(1),if the entry is being used. createAndGo(4),creat a new entry destroy(6),destory the entry.

tpVrrpVirtualIpCtrlTable.name: tpVrrpVirtualIpCtrlTable
tpVrrpVirtualIpCtrlTable.description: The table of addresses associated with this virtual router.

tpVrrpVirtualIpCtrlEntry.name: tpVrrpVirtualIpCtrlEntry
tpVrrpVirtualIpCtrlEntry.description: An entry in the table contains an IP address that is associated with a virtual router.

tpVrrpVirtualIpVrid.name: tpVrrpVirtualIpVrid
tpVrrpVirtualIpVrid.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).

tpVrrpVirtualIpAddress.name: tpVrrpVirtualIpAddress
tpVrrpVirtualIpAddress.description: The virtual IP address associated with a virtual router.

tpVrrpVirtualIpStatus.name: tpVrrpVirtualIpStatus
tpVrrpVirtualIpStatus.description: The following values are states: these values may be used as follow: active(1),if the entry is being used. createAndGo(4),creat a new entry destroy(6),destory the entry.

tpVrrpTrackCtrlTable.name: tpVrrpTrackCtrlTable
tpVrrpTrackCtrlTable.description: The table of ifindex tracked by the virtual router.

tpVrrpTrackCtrlEntry.name: tpVrrpTrackCtrlEntry
tpVrrpTrackCtrlEntry.description: An entry in the table contains the ifindex and reduced priority that is associated with a virtual router.

tpVrrpTrackVrid.name: tpVrrpTrackVrid
tpVrrpTrackVrid.description: This object contains the Virtual Router Identifier (VRID).

tpVrrpTrackInterface.name: tpVrrpTrackInterface
tpVrrpTrackInterface.description: The ifindex tracked by the virtual router.

tpVrrpTrackPriortiy.name: tpVrrpTrackPriortiy
tpVrrpTrackPriortiy.description: The object operate the priority of the virtual router when the interface tracked linkdown.

tpVrrpLinkState.name: tpVrrpLinkState
tpVrrpLinkState.description: The object display the status of the interface tracked .

tpVrrpTrackStatus.name: tpVrrpTrackStatus
tpVrrpTrackStatus.description: The following values are states: these values may be used as follow: active(1),if the entry is being used. createAndGo(4),creat a new entry destroy(6),destory the entry.

tpVrrpChecksumErrors.name: tpVrrpChecksumErrors
tpVrrpChecksumErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received with an invalid VRRP checksum value.

tpVrrpVersionErrors.name: tpVrrpVersionErrors
tpVrrpVersionErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received with an unknown or unsupported version number.

tpVrrpVridErrors.name: tpVrrpVridErrors
tpVrrpVridErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received with an invalid VRID for this virtual router.

tpvrrpStatsClear.name: tpvrrpStatsClear
tpvrrpStatsClear.description: The following values are states: these values may be used as follow: active(1),if the entry is being used. clear(0),set the entry to 0.

tpVrrpStatsEntry.name: tpVrrpStatsEntry
tpVrrpStatsEntry.description: An entry in the table, containing statistics information about a given virtual router.

tpVrrpStatsVrid.name: tpVrrpStatsVrid
tpVrrpStatsVrid.description: the VRID of the virtual router. It is used together with interface ID to specify the virtual router to operate statistics.

tpVrrpStatsVid.name: tpVrrpStatsVid
tpVrrpStatsVid.description: the interface ID of the virtual router. It is used together with VRID to specify the virtual router to operate statistics.

tpVrrpChecksumErr.name: tpVrrpChecksumErr
tpVrrpChecksumErr.description: The total number of VRRP packets received with an invalid VRRP checksum value by this virtual router.

tpVrrpVersionErr.name: tpVrrpVersionErr
tpVrrpVersionErr.description: The total number of VRRP packets received with an unknown or unsupported version number by this virtual router.

tpVrrpStatsBecomeMaster.name: tpVrrpStatsBecomeMaster
tpVrrpStatsBecomeMaster.description: The total number of times that this virtual router's state has transitioned to MASTER.

tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseRcvd.name: tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseRcvd
tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseRcvd.description: The total number of VRRP advertisements received by this virtual router.

tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseSent.name: tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseSent
tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseSent.description: The total number of VRRP advertisements sent by this virtual router.

tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseIntervalErrors.name: tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseIntervalErrors
tpvrrpStatsAdvertiseIntervalErrors.description: The total number of VRRP advertisement packets received for which the advertisement interval is different than the one configured for the local virtual router.

tpvrrpStatsAuthFailures.name: tpvrrpStatsAuthFailures
tpvrrpStatsAuthFailures.description: The total number of VRRP packets received that do not pass the authentication check.

tpvrrpStatsIpTtlErrors.name: tpvrrpStatsIpTtlErrors
tpvrrpStatsIpTtlErrors.description: The total number of VRRP packets received by the virtual router with IP TTL (Time-To-Live) not equal to 255.

tpvrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsRcvd.name: tpvrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsRcvd
tpvrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsRcvd.description: The total number of VRRP packets received by the virtual router with a priority of '0'.

tpvrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsSent.name: tpvrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsSent
tpvrrpStatsPriorityZeroPktsSent.description: The total number of VRRP packets sent by the virtual router with a priority of '0'.

tpvrrpStatsInvalidTypePktsRcvd.name: tpvrrpStatsInvalidTypePktsRcvd
tpvrrpStatsInvalidTypePktsRcvd.description: The number of VRRP packets received by the virtual router with an invalid value in the 'type' field.

tpvrrpStatsAddressListErrors.name: tpvrrpStatsAddressListErrors
tpvrrpStatsAddressListErrors.description: The total number of packets received for which the address list does not match the locally configured list for the virtual router.

tpvrrpStatsInvalidAuthType.name: tpvrrpStatsInvalidAuthType
tpvrrpStatsInvalidAuthType.description: The total number of packets received with an unknown authentication type.

tpvrrpStatsAuthTypeMismatch.name: tpvrrpStatsAuthTypeMismatch
tpvrrpStatsAuthTypeMismatch.description: The total number of packets received with 'Auth Type' not equal to the locally configured authentication method (`vrrpOperAuthType').

tpvrrpStatsPacketLengthErrors.name: tpvrrpStatsPacketLengthErrors
tpvrrpStatsPacketLengthErrors.description: The total number of packets received with a packet length less than the length of the VRRP header.
